WEBVTT



00:00:26.631 --> 00:00:29.175
Mr. Hwang Johan, you're free to go.

00:00:30.343 --> 00:00:32.053
Please check your belongings.

00:00:38.726 --> 00:00:40.103
Is everything there?

00:00:40.186 --> 00:00:41.187
Yes.

00:00:42.313 --> 00:00:43.731
Wait a second.

00:00:51.447 --> 00:00:53.158
You should wear this for a while.

00:00:56.578 --> 00:00:57.579
Okay.

00:01:12.218 --> 00:01:14.179
MISSED CALL FROM SUA
MISSED CALL FROM RYU

00:01:14.262 --> 00:01:15.388
SUA: PLEASE PICK UP

00:01:15.471 --> 00:01:16.931
RYU: ARE YOU OKAY? PLEASE REPLY

00:01:17.015 --> 00:01:17.891
CALLING RYU

00:01:29.110 --> 00:01:32.197
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable.

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:34.616
Please leave your message…

00:01:38.036 --> 00:01:39.495
What should we eat today?

00:01:40.288 --> 00:01:41.289
Today?

00:01:41.915 --> 00:01:44.751
Hey, did you see this?

00:01:44.834 --> 00:01:45.835
What?

00:01:47.212 --> 00:01:51.507
A pro boxer beat someone up
and got released? That's crazy.

00:01:52.008 --> 00:01:54.677
A civilian could die
if they're hit by a professional.

00:01:54.761 --> 00:01:58.348
I saw on the news
that he even threw his fights.

00:01:58.431 --> 00:02:00.350
-Threw fights?
-Yeah.

00:02:02.268 --> 00:02:05.563
Why would the police release
someone like that?

00:02:05.647 --> 00:02:08.066
That’s why they get criticized
all the time.

00:02:08.149 --> 00:02:09.192
So true.

00:02:32.966 --> 00:02:36.678
GAY BASTARD

00:02:51.276 --> 00:02:54.279
KANG SUNGMIN BOXING GYM

00:03:02.829 --> 00:03:03.830
Johan.

00:03:05.415 --> 00:03:06.249
You're here.

00:03:14.924 --> 00:03:16.509
Why are you here, Johan?

00:03:17.510 --> 00:03:18.386
Jisub.

00:03:18.469 --> 00:03:20.722
This place is going under because of you.

00:03:20.805 --> 00:03:21.848
That's enough.

00:03:25.393 --> 00:03:27.812
Don't worry about it. It's fine.

00:03:27.895 --> 00:03:30.189
No, it's not!

00:03:30.273 --> 00:03:32.483
I said it's fine!

00:03:35.737 --> 00:03:38.072
Do you have any idea
what he's been through?

00:03:40.450 --> 00:03:41.659
Coach.

00:03:41.743 --> 00:03:43.161
Are you for real?

00:03:43.244 --> 00:03:44.912
You still call him "Coach"?

00:03:44.996 --> 00:03:47.665
You hit a civilian and even fixed matches.

00:03:48.166 --> 00:03:50.376
The association wouldn't let this slide.

00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:51.753
Let go.

00:03:51.836 --> 00:03:53.588
-Well?
-I said let go!

00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:57.008
That's enough.

00:03:57.091 --> 00:03:58.551
You can go home now.

00:04:12.940 --> 00:04:14.275
Sorry.

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:16.778
That's what happened.

00:04:18.696 --> 00:04:21.282
I won't be able to employ you anymore.

00:04:23.284 --> 00:04:25.828
It's all my fault.

00:04:27.288 --> 00:04:30.124
This was all Shim's doing.

00:04:31.042 --> 00:04:33.920
And my way of doing things
is old-fashioned

00:04:34.712 --> 00:04:36.381
and outdated.

00:04:38.299 --> 00:04:40.259
You used to say that a lot too.

00:04:49.602 --> 00:04:52.563
I remember the first time you came here.

00:04:53.272 --> 00:04:54.816
I enjoyed

00:04:56.692 --> 00:05:02.031
getting to box with you.

00:05:08.162 --> 00:05:09.872
Don't push yourself too hard

00:05:10.665 --> 00:05:12.500
and take it easy in life.

00:05:14.085 --> 00:05:15.211
Got it?

00:05:23.136 --> 00:05:26.514
MISSED CALL FROM JOHAN

00:05:26.597 --> 00:05:27.723
Ryu, got a minute?

00:05:29.225 --> 00:05:30.560
Yes.

00:05:30.643 --> 00:05:32.770
We have an emergency admission tomorrow.

00:05:32.854 --> 00:05:34.480
Can you help me prepare?

00:05:34.981 --> 00:05:36.566
Got it.

00:05:41.821 --> 00:05:44.407
You loser!
I'll destroy everything important to you!

00:06:12.059 --> 00:06:13.394
I'm not a loser.

00:06:13.478 --> 00:06:15.271
I'm not a loser dog!

00:06:18.524 --> 00:06:19.734
I trust you.

00:06:19.817 --> 00:06:23.112
The way you never gave up
made you look stronger than anyone else.

00:06:23.196 --> 00:06:24.405
Go, Johan!

00:06:25.156 --> 00:06:27.325
It's always been just the two of us.

00:06:29.035 --> 00:06:30.953
-The soul.
-The soul?

00:06:31.037 --> 00:06:32.330
I'll protect it.

00:06:32.830 --> 00:06:36.626
To make that happen,
I'm going to destroy it.

00:06:45.259 --> 00:06:48.846
Why is it always me?!

00:07:02.735 --> 00:07:05.738
We have connected your call,
but there was no answer.

00:07:05.821 --> 00:07:08.282
Please leave a message after the tone.

00:07:33.474 --> 00:07:35.059
-Ryu?
-Oh, hello?

00:07:35.142 --> 00:07:36.519
Sorry for the sudden call.

00:07:37.478 --> 00:07:38.688
What should I do?

00:07:38.771 --> 00:07:40.982
Is Johan…

00:07:41.649 --> 00:07:43.109
Johan is…

00:07:45.528 --> 00:07:47.822
I've been calling him all this time.

00:07:48.990 --> 00:07:50.074
I, um…

00:07:50.157 --> 00:07:51.117
It'll be fine.

00:07:51.617 --> 00:07:54.453
Let's start with places
where we might find a lead.

00:07:55.079 --> 00:07:56.622
Yes.

00:07:56.706 --> 00:07:57.915
It'll be fine.

00:07:57.999 --> 00:08:00.585
We'll find him for sure.

00:08:00.668 --> 00:08:01.961
We will.

00:08:02.461 --> 00:08:05.089
Yes. Thank you.

00:08:05.172 --> 00:08:12.179
GAY BASTARD

00:08:17.226 --> 00:08:20.688
Johan!

00:09:16.702 --> 00:09:18.663
OUR DOORS WILL CLOSE ON APRIL 30TH

00:09:18.746 --> 00:09:20.748
It looks like they've shut down.

00:09:27.588 --> 00:09:29.465
What about the bar where it happened?

00:09:30.466 --> 00:09:31.926
Do you know where it is?

00:09:32.802 --> 00:09:33.803
Yes.

00:09:35.596 --> 00:09:36.639
I do.

00:09:45.856 --> 00:09:46.857
Which way?

00:09:46.941 --> 00:09:48.693
-It's this way.
-This way?

00:10:06.293 --> 00:10:08.087
You're Johan's little sister?

00:10:08.921 --> 00:10:10.089
Yes.

00:10:13.759 --> 00:10:16.595
Then are you perhaps Ryu?

00:10:18.514 --> 00:10:19.515
Ryu.

00:10:25.980 --> 00:10:28.190
Johan's told me a lot about you two.

00:10:29.108 --> 00:10:31.026
I didn't expect to meet you like this.

00:10:39.535 --> 00:10:41.120
Excuse me.

00:10:41.704 --> 00:10:43.330
Do you know where my brother is?

00:10:47.501 --> 00:10:53.549
Please tell us… where Johan is.

00:10:54.508 --> 00:10:56.093
Please.

00:10:56.677 --> 00:11:01.015
He told me not to tell anyone,
even if you two came here.

00:11:02.641 --> 00:11:05.311
Please, I'm begging you!

00:11:05.394 --> 00:11:07.438
Please stop.

00:11:07.521 --> 00:11:08.856
I'm begging you.

00:11:09.482 --> 00:11:10.900
Please don't do this.

00:11:12.443 --> 00:11:13.944
That kid…

00:11:17.490 --> 00:11:18.949
Please save him.

00:11:20.868 --> 00:11:23.871
I think he's at the abandoned factory
where he used to work.

00:11:24.747 --> 00:11:28.042
He said that's the only place left
where he can work.

00:11:28.918 --> 00:11:30.628
-Thank you.
-Take care.

00:11:30.711 --> 00:11:31.921
Thank you.

00:11:53.275 --> 00:11:59.240
NO TRESPASSING

00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:13.170
Johan!

00:12:14.547 --> 00:12:15.589
Open the door!

00:12:15.673 --> 00:12:17.842
-Johan!
-Johan!

00:12:47.413 --> 00:12:49.331
That's Johan's manga.

00:12:49.415 --> 00:12:50.416
Yeah.

00:13:02.970 --> 00:13:04.430
Johan!

00:13:04.513 --> 00:13:05.931
-Johan!
-Johan!

00:13:16.525 --> 00:13:17.359
Hey, wait!

00:13:24.158 --> 00:13:25.409
Johan!

00:13:37.004 --> 00:13:39.590
You're getting out of shape, huh?

00:13:40.758 --> 00:13:43.010
Why did you come here?

00:13:52.937 --> 00:13:57.399
Just leave me alone.

00:13:58.067 --> 00:14:00.194
You want me to leave you alone?

00:14:02.655 --> 00:14:03.989
Don't you get it?

00:14:05.866 --> 00:14:07.159
It's…

00:14:08.702 --> 00:14:10.204
It's all over for me now.

00:14:12.289 --> 00:14:14.375
If you get involved with me…

00:14:17.836 --> 00:14:22.257
bad things will happen to you too.

00:14:32.768 --> 00:14:34.395
Why are you laughing?

00:14:40.734 --> 00:14:42.653
You were trying to protect it, right?

00:14:47.658 --> 00:14:49.159
Your soul.

00:15:31.410 --> 00:15:32.619
You're…

00:15:33.746 --> 00:15:38.083
You're the one person
I didn't want to see me like this.

00:15:52.639 --> 00:15:53.640
Johan.

00:15:58.771 --> 00:16:01.774
Let's live together in Japan.

00:16:57.371 --> 00:16:59.373
Let's eat.

00:17:07.965 --> 00:17:09.424
Masisseo.

00:17:11.844 --> 00:17:13.137
This is good!

00:17:34.825 --> 00:17:36.243
Earlier…

00:17:38.162 --> 00:17:39.163
Hm?

00:17:42.124 --> 00:17:44.835
You mentioned living together in Japan.

00:17:46.962 --> 00:17:48.088
Did you mean it?

00:17:49.756 --> 00:17:50.757
Oh.

00:17:53.552 --> 00:17:54.553
Yeah.

00:17:56.221 --> 00:17:57.055
I meant it.

00:18:22.372 --> 00:18:23.373
I…

00:18:25.709 --> 00:18:27.336
have a dream.

00:18:27.836 --> 00:18:28.837
Hm?

00:18:32.466 --> 00:18:34.426
I want to go to university

00:18:36.053 --> 00:18:36.887
in Japan.

00:18:40.182 --> 00:18:41.183
Yeah.

00:18:42.517 --> 00:18:43.518
Good idea.

00:18:55.405 --> 00:18:56.573
Thank you

00:18:57.824 --> 00:18:59.451
for coming.

00:19:02.454 --> 00:19:03.288
What'd you say?

00:19:10.545 --> 00:19:11.546
I won't say it again.

00:19:44.705 --> 00:19:49.001
"Anyway, in life,

00:19:50.085 --> 00:19:56.842
it is better to spend your time
doing what you enjoy."

00:20:09.271 --> 00:20:10.814
I'm home.

00:20:10.897 --> 00:20:12.190
Welcome back.

00:20:17.237 --> 00:20:20.699
Whoa, this looks so good.

00:20:21.408 --> 00:20:22.701
Wow.

00:20:24.411 --> 00:20:26.663
Wash your hands first.

00:20:27.456 --> 00:20:29.291
-Yeah, okay.
-Yeah.

00:20:32.002 --> 00:20:35.213
-Oh, help yourself to rice.
-Okay.

00:20:35.297 --> 00:20:36.131
Yeah.

00:20:42.763 --> 00:20:43.805
Stop moving.

00:20:45.307 --> 00:20:48.143
It's impossible to eat without moving.

00:20:52.773 --> 00:20:56.902
I'm going to a farewell party
for the head of the caretaker department,

00:20:56.985 --> 00:20:58.820
so I don't need dinner tomorrow.

00:21:00.405 --> 00:21:01.656
Oh, I see.

00:21:02.741 --> 00:21:05.410
Mmm. This is good.

00:21:06.912 --> 00:21:08.622
Of course it is.

00:21:14.378 --> 00:21:19.007
Hey, are you free this weekend
to meet with Sumiko and Seiichi?

00:21:19.508 --> 00:21:21.259
Yeah, I'm free.

00:21:22.177 --> 00:21:25.222
I have no plans other than my shift
at the convenience store.

00:21:28.266 --> 00:21:31.520
I hope you get to work
at the Korean language school.

00:21:31.603 --> 00:21:33.522
Easier said than done.

00:21:33.605 --> 00:21:36.108
It's difficult without a degree.

00:21:40.112 --> 00:21:42.155
I gotta study
for my caregiver training too.

00:21:42.239 --> 00:21:43.657
Don't just move like that.

00:21:43.740 --> 00:21:45.242
I'm getting seconds.

00:21:46.660 --> 00:21:47.661
Okay, then.

00:21:59.381 --> 00:22:01.466
-He's good.
-Johan's amazing!

00:22:03.218 --> 00:22:05.846
Come on, jump!

00:22:05.929 --> 00:22:08.640
Wait. Let's take a break.

00:22:08.723 --> 00:22:10.225
I give up.

00:22:11.059 --> 00:22:13.478
Is it your arm? Or maybe it's the snap?

00:22:13.562 --> 00:22:15.313
Yeah, it's all in the snap.

00:22:16.022 --> 00:22:17.441
Water, please.

00:22:17.524 --> 00:22:18.442
I'm no match.

00:22:18.525 --> 00:22:19.359
-Here.
-Here.

00:22:19.443 --> 00:22:20.861
-Oh, thanks.
-Thanks.

00:22:20.944 --> 00:22:22.821
-You're way too tired.
-I'm beat.

00:22:22.904 --> 00:22:24.197
All right.

00:22:24.698 --> 00:22:25.907
-Then…
-Then…

00:22:25.991 --> 00:22:27.242
If you please.

00:22:27.325 --> 00:22:28.952
If you please.

00:22:30.829 --> 00:22:33.165
All right, my junior, you write.

00:22:33.248 --> 00:22:35.542
You need me to write it first.

00:22:36.209 --> 00:22:37.919
-Okay, I'm filling it in.
-Okay.

00:22:38.003 --> 00:22:39.337
All right.

00:22:39.838 --> 00:22:40.922
I'll stamp it.

00:22:41.006 --> 00:22:42.507
-Yes, please.
-Yes, please.

00:22:42.591 --> 00:22:45.719
HWANG JOHAN

00:22:45.802 --> 00:22:48.054
-Wow.
-Wow.

00:22:50.098 --> 00:22:51.349
All right.

00:22:52.976 --> 00:22:53.894
I'll stamp it.

00:22:53.977 --> 00:22:55.187
Yes, please.

00:22:55.270 --> 00:22:59.900
RYU NARUTAKI

00:22:59.983 --> 00:23:01.943
-Yeah.
-Wow.

00:23:02.027 --> 00:23:03.153
Thank you.

00:23:03.737 --> 00:23:04.779
-Congrats.
-Congrats.

00:23:04.863 --> 00:23:06.323
Thank you, both of you.

00:23:06.990 --> 00:23:08.700
I'm so glad.

00:23:09.993 --> 00:23:11.995
Wow, it's nice. Neat writing.

00:23:12.871 --> 00:23:17.584
Man, it feels special
having you sign this, Ryu.

00:23:18.251 --> 00:23:19.794
That's my line.

00:23:20.921 --> 00:23:22.214
Thank you too, Johan.

00:23:22.297 --> 00:23:23.131
It's nothing.

00:23:28.220 --> 00:23:29.554
Guess what?

00:23:30.472 --> 00:23:31.473
Hm?

00:23:35.227 --> 00:23:36.478
We're expecting.

00:23:38.605 --> 00:23:39.606
Huh?

00:23:44.236 --> 00:23:45.237
A baby.

00:23:49.324 --> 00:23:50.242
What?!

00:23:51.952 --> 00:23:53.203
-Seriously?
-Yeah.

00:23:53.286 --> 00:23:54.412
Yeah.

00:23:54.496 --> 00:23:55.497
Up we go.

00:23:55.997 --> 00:23:56.998
Congrats, Sumiko.

00:23:57.749 --> 00:23:58.667
Thank you.

00:23:58.750 --> 00:24:00.126
Congratulations.

00:24:02.337 --> 00:24:06.633
I had bad morning sickness,
but I'm feeling better now.

00:24:07.968 --> 00:24:11.137
We wanted to tell you guys in person.

00:24:11.638 --> 00:24:12.472
I see.

00:24:12.556 --> 00:24:13.848
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:24:16.560 --> 00:24:18.019
In that case…

00:24:20.939 --> 00:24:22.399
Can I feel it?

00:24:23.984 --> 00:24:24.985
Of course.

00:24:26.653 --> 00:24:28.321
Hey, you don't have to do that.

00:24:28.405 --> 00:24:31.074
No, no. All right.

00:24:38.873 --> 00:24:41.876
-Whoa.
-What?

00:24:42.502 --> 00:24:43.670
-Wow.
-Huh?

00:24:43.753 --> 00:24:45.755
-Wow!
-What is it?

00:24:46.673 --> 00:24:47.507
You try too.

00:24:47.591 --> 00:24:49.175
-Wait, can I?
-Yeah.

00:24:51.219 --> 00:24:52.470
-Excuse me.
-Go ahead.

00:24:56.975 --> 00:24:58.018
-Whoa.
-Right?

00:24:58.101 --> 00:24:58.935
Yeah.

00:24:59.978 --> 00:25:01.021
What was that?

00:25:01.104 --> 00:25:02.105
-Right?
-Yeah.

00:25:02.188 --> 00:25:03.023
Man.

00:25:03.106 --> 00:25:06.067
Wow, there's a baby in here, huh?

00:25:06.151 --> 00:25:07.152
Yeah.

00:25:08.737 --> 00:25:11.615
All right. You're up next, Ryu.

00:25:11.698 --> 00:25:13.283
-Huh?
-Huh?

00:25:13.783 --> 00:25:18.496
I couldn't beat you at ice hockey,
but I won't lose at this.

00:25:18.580 --> 00:25:19.831
Come on, let's do this.

00:25:19.914 --> 00:25:21.666
What? We're still playing?

00:25:21.750 --> 00:25:24.544
Of course. Come on, move it!

00:25:24.628 --> 00:25:26.880
-We were talking here.
-No, let's play.

00:25:26.963 --> 00:25:27.922
Come on.

00:25:28.006 --> 00:25:29.716
-Have fun!
-Ugh, jeez.

00:25:29.799 --> 00:25:32.927
-Hey, run. Let's go!
-I don't wanna.

00:25:33.011 --> 00:25:34.346
-Go!
-Jeez!

00:25:34.846 --> 00:25:37.057
What? Is he playing by himself?

00:25:37.140 --> 00:25:38.683
Ready? Here!

00:25:38.767 --> 00:25:41.144
-It came right back at you.
-Come on! Run!

00:25:49.653 --> 00:25:51.154
About Ryu…

00:25:54.240 --> 00:25:55.617
Take care of him, okay?

00:26:02.540 --> 00:26:03.750
Leave him to me.

00:26:07.754 --> 00:26:09.756
You gotta jump!

00:26:12.509 --> 00:26:14.094
Wasn't that amazing?

00:26:15.053 --> 00:26:16.054
What was?

00:26:16.930 --> 00:26:21.017
I was just thinking how amazing
Seiichi and Sumiko are.

00:26:21.101 --> 00:26:22.143
Hmm.

00:26:22.227 --> 00:26:24.145
They're having a kid.

00:26:25.480 --> 00:26:26.481
Yeah.

00:26:34.823 --> 00:26:38.493
Do you want kids too?

00:26:39.703 --> 00:26:42.664
Hmm. Kids, huh?

00:26:43.164 --> 00:26:45.125
I've never really thought about it.

00:26:47.836 --> 00:26:49.754
-I see.
-Yeah.

00:26:53.091 --> 00:26:56.302
But it definitely felt like a miracle.

00:27:06.938 --> 00:27:08.356
A miracle.

00:27:09.023 --> 00:27:10.024
Yeah.

00:27:15.989 --> 00:27:18.742
The fact that I'm here is a miracle too.

00:27:19.451 --> 00:27:20.452
Hm?

00:27:22.537 --> 00:27:25.623
I just happened to meet you in Germany.

00:27:27.041 --> 00:27:28.376
And right now, somehow…

00:27:30.420 --> 00:27:33.339
we're living together in Japan.

00:27:38.970 --> 00:27:40.346
It's a miracle, isn't it?

00:27:41.347 --> 00:27:42.348
That's true.

00:27:45.101 --> 00:27:46.269
It's a miracle.

00:27:56.279 --> 00:27:57.530
All right.

00:27:58.990 --> 00:28:00.033
I'm off.

00:28:00.116 --> 00:28:01.534
Okay. Have a good day.

00:28:03.495 --> 00:28:04.788
I'm off.

00:28:04.871 --> 00:28:06.915
"Have a good day."

00:28:09.125 --> 00:28:11.711
-Call me if anything happens.
-I will.

00:28:13.254 --> 00:28:16.132
-Promise.
-I know. I will.

00:28:16.216 --> 00:28:17.842
-Okay, see you later.
-See you.

00:28:17.926 --> 00:28:19.302
-Be careful.
-Okay.

00:28:19.385 --> 00:28:26.392
HAPPY NAME DICTIONARY FOR BABIES

00:28:29.854 --> 00:28:32.190
-Phew.
-Hey, watch your back!

00:28:32.273 --> 00:28:34.025
-I'm fine.
-Isn't it heavy?

00:28:34.108 --> 00:28:36.903
Not at all.
Remember, I'm Super Scrappy Seiichi!

00:28:36.986 --> 00:28:37.946
Hey, over here.

00:28:38.029 --> 00:28:39.656
-Yes.
-Bring out that thing.

00:28:39.739 --> 00:28:40.865
Okay.

00:28:41.950 --> 00:28:43.451
There we go.

00:28:45.703 --> 00:28:47.080
-This here…
-Yes?

00:28:47.163 --> 00:28:51.876
We know it's a bit late,
but this one's from us.

00:28:52.544 --> 00:28:54.087
A wedding gift.

00:28:54.170 --> 00:28:57.632
-What? No way. Really?
-Yeah.

00:28:57.715 --> 00:29:00.510
And your baby's coming soon too.
How exciting.

00:29:01.386 --> 00:29:03.513
Yes. Thank you very much.

00:29:06.057 --> 00:29:07.642
Well, then. Goodbye.

00:31:39.919 --> 00:31:42.839
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura